result_quotes: Medical Student: OK, do you have any other symptoms? like a runny nose, sore throat? Anything like that?
Medical Student: OK, and have you had any surgeries or have been hospitalized before?
Patient: I did have tubes in my ears when I was little, but that's it though.
Medical Student: OK, were you having night sweats?
Patient: My bed wasn't drenched or anything but I was sweating.
Medical Student: OK. Has your sleep or appetite changed at all?
Patient: I didn't sleep very good last night. I just don't feel very rested this morning.
Medical Student: OK, and do you have any allergies?
Patient: Uhm, just environmental stuff I think, just, like in the springtime, I'll get itchy eyes or a runny nose.
Medical Student: Have you been in contact with anyone that's been sick recently?
Patient: I don't think so. I work at the Toyota factory and there have been a few people that have been sick who worked there? But I don't think I've been in contact with them.
Patient: Yeah, probably like last night, this morning when I was laying down and just felt a bit tired and achy?
Medical Student: OK, and is it kind of like a pressure like pain? Is it pulsating pain? How would you describe it?
Patient: I would say it's more of a pressure, yeah.
